content.body: Alex Stupak, the chef behind the Empell√≥n family of restaurants, turns to American cuisine at this contemporary Midtown stunner. For Stupak, that means adding new twists to classic dishes (deviled egg floating island or gai lan Caesar, anyone?). Whatever you do, don‚Äôt sleep on the desserts: Stupak‚Äôs forte, honed with years spent at WD-50 and Alinea, is as a pastry chef.¬†
content.name: why_we_like_it

about.body: Located in Midtown Manhattan, Mischa is a New American restaurant by Alex Stupak. The menus showcase a variety of dishes that reflect a range of culinary interests and ideas, imbued with a sensibility indicative of our New York City home. The beverage menu mirrors this as well, with fresh takes on classic cocktails alongside a locally-sourced beer list and an international selection of wine and spirits.

need_to_know.body: Mischa is located within The Hugh at 157 East 53rd Street. Enter via the 53rd Street entrance in the middle of the block. Directly to your left on the mezzanine level, take the small staircase up to the Mischa host stand. Our ADA-accessible entryway is available on 53rd Street at street level east of Lexington Avenue and west of the main Mischa entrance.

content.body: Tucked in the heart of the West Village, Empell√≥n Taqueria puts a modern cheffy spin on everything from queso to tacos (don‚Äôt overlook the brussels sprouts one), courtesy of chef-owner Alex Stupak of Alinea and wd~50 fame. Do order the salsa flight and keep your eyes peeled for the special taco drops every other Tuesday; previous creations have taken inspiration from Mexican specialties, French ravigote sauce, and even pumpkin spice latte.
